I am sure if I dined here in person, I'd have had much better experience. However, this review is for delivery - the food was pretty good for a delivery!  Black Garlic Tsukemen: I really enjoy this type of thick ramen noodles, but just for my personal taste I thought the broth flavor could be stronger.  Tako Agedashi: I did not know what to expect from this one but I thoroughly enjoyed this. I'm sure it'd have tasted even better when eaten fresh.  Golden Pork Bun: this one was slightly disappointing since the pork was dry and tough.  Shiokara (fermented squid): ordered this one for fun since I never had anything like it. If you don't like fishy taste, I discourage you to order it. It tastes pretty interesting, but was hard to finish.  Matcha Tiramisu & Vanilla Ice Cream: not bad at all, especially since I ate after I finished eating everything else and the ice cream was barely melted after arriving from delivery and being outside so long

If you want something healthy and you're trying to lose weight...this is the wrong place. But if you want some delicious rich ramen broth then you have struck gold..or should I say you have struck Golden Pork!  On our recent trip to Oahu a local friend recommended this place. And it most definitely did not disappoint.  Like most places in Hawaii parking is a bit difficult. But once you walk in compared to most Hawaiian places it's actually fairly good-sized. But the real pleasure is when you get your Ramen.  My kids had the Original Ramen and I had the spicy miso.  They are both outstanding.  The base broth is super rich and creamy. So much so that the broth is able to clean onto the noodles. Some spicy miso ramens actually have a spicy ground pork mixture. This does not, but just spicy miso paste. Normally this would have disappointed me. However in this case, the broth was so rich it did not need any additional pork. I believe that Tonkatsu Ramen uses melted pork lard inside the soup. This place must use extra. I can imagine that if the soup were to cool down it would actually coagulate. This Ramen is probably not so good for your heart but your tummy will love you for it.  I would have rated this place a 5, however the chasu was not as tender as it could have been.   We also had an appetizer of gyoza and cucumbers. Gyoza ok.  Cucumbers lacked flavor.  Not marinated, but rather had spicy chili oil drizzled.  For the Ramen alone we went there twice.
Gyoza the best I’ve had.  Crispy one side, soft the other, with ingredients shining through.  Worth coming for gyoza alone.  Spicy Ramen super good as well.  Busy at lunch.

I was recommended Golden Pork by a co-worker, and after finding out where it was, I discovered that it's really close to my residence. Everything that I've had there has tasted better than Agu and the prices can't be beat either. There's a wide selection of sake from what I've seen (but I don't drink alcohol, so that's a moot point). I haven't had an opportunity to try all of the appetizers, but I really do recommend the golden pork buns. They're so good that if you order the 2 piece plate, you won't want to share. As far as the main courses, so far I've had the classic and black garlic ton-kotsu, and my girlfriend had one is the tsukemen dishes. Those are the first bowls of ramen that made me finish all of the broth since I was in Japan. That's how good they were.  Lastly, don't forget to get a stamp card and be a complete hipster, and post to Instagram! Get a free ramen or tsukemen after every 10 stamps!
